      },
      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask whether the patient is looking for a primary care \nprovider or a specialist.\n\nSay something like: \"Are you looking for a primary \ncare doctor, or do you need to see a specialist for \nsomething specific?\"\n\nIf the user says primary care: \"Got it — we'll set \nyou up with one of our primary care providers.\"\n\nIf the user says specialist and names the type (e.g. \n\"dermatologist\", \"cardiologist\"): Acknowledge it: \n\"Got it — so you're looking for a [specialty] \nreferral.\"\n\nIf the user says specialist but doesn't know what \nkind: \"No problem — based on what you've described, \nthe clinic can point you in the right direction at \nyour visit.\"\n\nIf the user says \"both\" or \"I need a regular doctor \nbut also have a specific issue\": \"Got it — we can \nstart with a primary care visit and they can refer \nyou to a specialist from there if needed.\"\n\nIf the user isn't sure: \"That's okay — primary care \nis usually a great starting point. They can evaluate \neverything and refer you to a specialist if anything \nneeds a closer look.\"\n\nIf the user doesn't want to answer: \"No worries — \nwe'll start with primary care and the doctor can \nguide you from there.\"\n\nOne ask is enough. Default to primary care if unclear."
      }
    },
